One useful tip is that when the Runnable you provide finishes executing, the game loop or UI may not have updated yet.
To address this issue, I typically have each unit test submit one or more Runnables for different tasks.
Between the execution of these Runnables, my base test runner class pauses for 10 UI frames (using Gdx.graphics.getFrameId()).
This strategy enables me to, for example, submit a Runnable that alters the game state, followed by another Runnable that captures a screenshot for comparison against expected results.

